<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 06 at 8:08AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG AFFECTING SOUTH PADRE ISLAND...
Satellite imagery and webcams indicate areas of fog persisting
across the coastal sections of Kenedy, Willacy, and Cameron
Counties. The fog is reducing visibility on South Padre Island and
the Queen Isabella Causeway to less than one mile.
These areas of fog are expected to persist through the late
morning hours.
Motorists, especially on South Padre Island and the Causeway, are
urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and avoid
following other vehicles too closely.</description>
